<caption pageId="4" pageNumber="289" startId="4.[136,229,1801,1823]" targetBox="[166,1428,206,1773]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1801,1967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="289">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,252,1801,1823]" pageId="4" pageNumber="289">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
General morphological details of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lagunday &amp; V. B. Amoroso" authorityYear="2022" box="[571,776,1801,1822]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nepenthaceae" genus="Nepenthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="4" pageNumber="289" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="candalaga">
<emphasis box="[571,776,1801,1822]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="289">Nepenthes candalaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[786,812,1801,1823]" pageId="4" pageNumber="289">A)</emphasis>
habit with aerial pitchers, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1058,1082,1801,1823]" pageId="4" pageNumber="289">B)</emphasis>
infructescence with dehisced capsules, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,161,1837,1859]" pageId="4" pageNumber="289">C)</emphasis>
leaf lamina showing winged petioles, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[529,554,1837,1859]" pageId="4" pageNumber="289">D)</emphasis>
lateral view of aerial pitchers, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[850,874,1837,1859]" pageId="4" pageNumber="289">E)</emphasis>
lateral view of aerial pitchers, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1170,1192,1837,1859]" pageId="4" pageNumber="289">F)</emphasis>
aerial pitcher long section, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,163,1873,1895]" pageId="4" pageNumber="289">G)</emphasis>
close up of dehiscing capsules, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[472,499,1873,1895]" pageId="4" pageNumber="289">H)</emphasis>
seed, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[560,577,1873,1895]" pageId="4" pageNumber="289">I)</emphasis>
adaxial and abaxial surface of the lid, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[950,970,1873,1895]" pageId="4" pageNumber="289">J)</emphasis>
lid spur, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1060,1087,1873,1895]" pageId="4" pageNumber="289">K)</emphasis>
lid appendage, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1239,1263,1873,1895]" pageId="4" pageNumber="289">L)</emphasis>
peristome showing teeth and nectar glands, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[369,400,1909,1931]" pageId="4" pageNumber="289">M)</emphasis>
waxy zone, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[522,547,1909,1931]" pageId="4" pageNumber="289">N)</emphasis>
digestive zone showing digestive glands, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[953,980,1909,1931]" pageId="4" pageNumber="289">O)</emphasis>
aerial pitcher wings. Scale bars: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1299,1429,1909,1931]" pageId="4" pageNumber="289">B, C, D, E, F</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1442,1451,1909,1930]" pageId="4" pageNumber="289">I</emphasis>
= 1 cm; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[216,443,1945,1967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="289">G, H, J, K, L, M, N, O</emphasis>
= 1 mm. Photographs by N.E. Lagunday.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,158,616]" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">
Noteworthy flora observed in the site were 
<taxonomicName authority="Tandang, Galindon &amp; A. S. Rob." authorityName="Tandang, Galindon &amp; A. S. Rob." box="[688,1279,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loranthaceae" genus="Amylotheca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Santalales" pageId="5" pageNumber="290" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cleofei">
<emphasis box="[688,904,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">Amylotheca cleofei</emphasis>
Tandang, Galindon &amp; A.S. Rob.
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation author="Tandang, D. N. &amp; Galindon, J. M. M. &amp; Lagunday, N. E. &amp; Coritico, F. P. &amp; Amoroso, V. B. &amp; Robinson, A. S." pageId="5" pageNumber="290" pagination="113 - 120" refId="ref5068" refString="Tandang, D. N., Galindon, J. M. M., Lagunday, N. E., Coritico, F. P., Amoroso, V. B. &amp; Robinson, A. S. (2021) Amylotheca cleofei sp. nov. (Loranthaceae), a new species and genus record for the Philippines. Phytotaxa 507 (1): 113 - 120. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 507.1.7" type="journal article" year="2021">
Tandang 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">et al.</emphasis>
2021: 114
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Mansell &amp; Suarez" authorityName="Mansell &amp; Suarez" box="[358,822,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nepenthaceae" genus="Nepenthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="290" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nebularum">
<emphasis box="[358,605,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">Nepenthes nebularum</emphasis>
Mansell &amp; Suarez
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Mansell, G. &amp; Suarez, W." box="[863,1214,194,220]" pageId="5" pageNumber="290" pagination="132 - 139" refId="ref4365" refString="Mansell, G. &amp; Suarez, W. (2016) Nepenthes nebularum, a new species from Mindanao, Philippines. Carnivorous Plant Newsletter 45: 132 - 139. https: // doi. org / 10.55360 / cpn 454. gm 291" type="journal article" year="2016">Mansell &amp; Suarez (2016: 133)</bibRefCitation>
which can easily be recognized in the field in having cylindrical pitchers and broad leaves. The later was recorded in Mt. Mayo, Tarragona, Mati (
<bibRefCitation author="Mansell, G. &amp; Suarez, W." box="[203,471,266,292]" pageId="5" pageNumber="290" pagination="132 - 139" refId="ref4365" refString="Mansell, G. &amp; Suarez, W. (2016) Nepenthes nebularum, a new species from Mindanao, Philippines. Carnivorous Plant Newsletter 45: 132 - 139. https: // doi. org / 10.55360 / cpn 454. gm 291" type="journal article" year="2016">Mansell &amp; Suarez 2016</bibRefCitation>
) and the former in Mt. Hamiguitan Range Wildlife Sanctuary, 
<collectingRegion box="[1168,1340,266,293]" country="Philippines" name="Davao Oriental" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">Davao Oriental</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Tandang, D. N. &amp; Galindon, J. M. M. &amp; Lagunday, N. E. &amp; Coritico, F. P. &amp; Amoroso, V. B. &amp; Robinson, A. S." pageId="5" pageNumber="290" pagination="113 - 120" refId="ref5068" refString="Tandang, D. N., Galindon, J. M. M., Lagunday, N. E., Coritico, F. P., Amoroso, V. B. &amp; Robinson, A. S. (2021) Amylotheca cleofei sp. nov. (Loranthaceae), a new species and genus record for the Philippines. Phytotaxa 507 (1): 113 - 120. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 507.1.7" type="journal article" year="2021">
Tandang 
<emphasis box="[136,196,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[290,400,302,329]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loranthaceae" genus="Amylotheca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Santalales" pageId="5" pageNumber="290" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cleofei">
<emphasis box="[290,400,302,329]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">A. cleofei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was observed along the river trails while 
<taxonomicName box="[898,1055,302,328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nepenthaceae" genus="Nepenthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="290" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nebularum">
<emphasis box="[898,1055,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">N. nebularum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
populations were observed in the TLMRF and TUMRF (
<quantity box="[395,551,338,365]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="5" pageNumber="290" unit="m" value="1800.0" valueMax="1900.0" valueMin="1700.0">1700–1900 m</quantity>
asl) epiphytic on tree branches 
<quantity box="[907,1006,338,365]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="290" unit="m" value="12.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="10.0">10–15 m</quantity>
high.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,158,616]" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,398,374,400]" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lagunday &amp; V. B. Amoroso" authorityYear="2022" box="[426,667,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nepenthaceae" genus="Nepenthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="290" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="candalaga">
<emphasis box="[426,667,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">Nepenthes candalaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
morphologically falls under 
<taxonomicName authority="Blanco (1837: 805)" authorityName="Blanco" authorityPageNumber="805" authorityYear="1837" box="[989,1451,374,401]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nepenthaceae" genus="Nepenthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="290" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Alata">
<emphasis box="[989,1106,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">Nepenthes</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[1168,1229,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">Alata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Blanco, F. M." box="[1235,1451,374,401]" pageId="5" pageNumber="290" refId="ref3139" refString="Blanco, F. M. (1837) Nepenthes. Flora de Filipinas. Santo Thomas [printers] por D. Candido Lopez, Manila, 619 pp." type="book" year="1837">Blanco (1837: 805)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
displaying winged petioles and lids with basal ridges producing appendages.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,158,616]" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,442,446,472]" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">Conservation status:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lagunday &amp; V. B. Amoroso" authorityYear="2022" box="[470,717,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nepenthaceae" genus="Nepenthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="290" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="candalaga">
<emphasis box="[470,717,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">Nepenthes candalaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is assessed here as Critically Endangered (CR] based on the criterion B1ab(i) of 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN Standards &amp; Petitions Committee" box="[360,514,482,508]" pageId="5" pageNumber="290" refId="ref4119" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Committee (2022) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 15. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Committee. Available from: https: // www. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed 17 May 2022)" type="book" year="2022">IUCN (2022)</bibRefCitation>
. The extent of occurrence (EOO) is less than 
<quantity box="[1021,1092,482,508]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="290" unit="km" value="10.0">10 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[1092,1100,482,496]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">2</superScript>
. The species suffers the habitat loss because of the deforestation and typhoons as part of the mountain was significantly damaged by Typhoon Pablo in 2012. The species is known only from the Mt. Candalaga and is likely to be endemic to the mountain, which faces threats of deforestation and habitat loss without legislative protection.
</paragraph>
